{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/101387", "id": 1045540529, "node_id": "PR_kwDOAAsO6M4-Ua6x", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/101387", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/101387.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/101387.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/101387", "number": 101387, "state": "open", "locked": false, "title": "Added `interrupt` function for `std::process::Child`", "user": {"login": "JonathanWoollett-Light", "id": 16856679, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2ODU2Njc5", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16856679?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light", "html_url": "https://github.com/JonathanWoollett-Light", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/JonathanWoollett-Light/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Added an `interrupt` function to [`std::process::Child`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/process/struct.Child.html) which acts similar to the [`kill`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/process/struct.Child.html#method.kill) function but uses the `SIGINT` signal instead of `SIGKILL`. This allows the process to catch the signal and gracefully exit.\r\n\r\nWhen working with binaries this is very important, considering a test where you need to spawn a server, interact with this server, then shutdown the server (this server may create local resources which require manual cleanup) (a little easier and safer than `unsafe { libc::kill(child.id() as i32, libc::SIGINT); }`).\r\n```rust\r\n#[test]\r\nfn stress_test() {\r\n    let server = std::process::Command::new(\"cargo\")\r\n            .args([\"run\", \"--bin\", \"my-server\"])\r\n            .spawn()\r\n            .unwrap();\r\n    // Some interaction\r\n    server.interrupt();\r\n   // Some finishing work\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt is better practice to interrupt applications to allow graceful shutdowns than to kill applications as this may leave remnants the application was not able to clean up. Really killing should only be used when applications are un-trusted or refuse to gracefully exit.\r\n\r\nI would argue, `interrupt` should probably be more commonly used than [`kill`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/process/struct.Child.html#method.kill).\r\n\r\nAlthough this is not changed in this PR, it might make sense in the future for [`std::process::Child`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/process/struct.Child.html) to implement [`std::ops::Drop`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/ops/trait.Drop.html) like:\r\n```rust\r\nimpl std::ops::Drop for std::process::Child {\r\n    fn drop(&mut self) {\r\n        self.interrupt();\r\n    } \r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe Fuschia implementation currently simply mimics `kill` I will look into Fuschia to see if I can fix this (I currently know basically nothing here).\r\n\r\nACP: https://github.com/rust-lang/libs-team/issues/97", "created_at": "2022-09-03T18:51:21Z", "updated_at": "2023-05-15T17:19:09Z", "closed_at": null, "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "6c37afaea0a82912cb5c4e371795d3665bc32d34", "assignee": {"login": "joshtriplett", "id": 162737, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MjczNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/162737?v=4", "gravatar_i